ys%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jeremy%20Siegel%20Wharton%20CNBC%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f353b28b4bb1c001df52ff0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222001%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EScott%20Mlyn%2FCNBC%2FNBCU%20Photo%20Bank%2FNBCUniversal%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAmerica's%20entry%20into%20the%20Israel-Iran%20conflict%20has%20markets%20on%20edge.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20Jeremy%20Siegel%20predicts%20that%20stocks%20can%20still%20soar%20to%20fresh%20records.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Wharton%20professor%20views%20the%20market's%20muted%20reaction%20as%20a%20positive%20indicator.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20attacks%20on%20Iranian%20nuclear%20facilities%20over%20the%20weekend%20have%20sparked%20fresh%20anxiety%20in%20markets%2C%20but%20there's%20a%20scenario%20in%20which%20stocks%20can%20soar%20to%20new%20records%20amid%20the%20conflict.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20according%20to%20Jeremy%20Siegel%2C%20the%20chief%20economist%20of%20Wisdom%20Tree%20and%20a%20professor%20of%20Finance%20at%20The%20Wharton%20School%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%2C%20who%20said%20that%20the%20development%20could%20ultimately%20be%20a%20positive%20for%20stocks.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESiegel%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2025%2F06%2F23%2Fjeremy-siegel-says-investors-are-viewing-the-us-bombings-as-a-success-to-neutralize-iran.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNBC%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Monday%20that%2C%20as%20he%20sees%20it%2C%20the%20market%20is%20likely%20to%20continue%20edging%20higher%20in%20the%20short%20term.%20The%20economist%20predicts%20that%20%26quot%3Bnew%20all-time%20highs%20in%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20are%20certainly%20attainable%20over%20the%20next%20several%20weeks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20his%20thesis%20is%20contingent%20on%20Iran%20taking%20no%20retaliatory%20action%20towards%20the%20US.%20Leaders%20in%20Iran%20have%20%26quot%3Bvowed%20to%20respond%2C%26quot%3B%20stating%20that%20it%20%26quot%3Breserves%20all%20options.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20he%20is%20not%20opposed%20to%20using%20further%20military%20force%20if%20Iran%20chooses%20to%20escalate%20the%20conflict%20further.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20market's%20reaction%20has%20been%20muted%20so%20far%2C%20with%20minimal%20price%20action%20among%20major%20indexes%20on%20Monday%20and%20oil%20slipping%20back%20down%20after%20initially%20spiking%20after%20the%20US%20attacks.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESiegel%20described%20the%20attack%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20success%20to%20neutralize%20Iran%2C%26quot%3B%20noting%20that%20he%20saw%20this%20as%20ultimately%20being%20positive%20for%20stocks%2C%20as%20it%20would%20likely%20lead%20to%20a%20faster%20resolution%20being%20reached%20for%20the%20countries%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20believes%20major%20US%20stock%20indexes%20can%20reach%20new%20highs%20if%20the%20conflict%20does%20not%20persist%20and%20Iran%20does%20not%20escalate%20further%2C%20which%20he%20seems%20to%20see%20as%20the%20most%20likely%20scenario.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20most%20people%20agree%20they%20are%20farther%20away%20from%20producing%20a%20bomb%20than%20they%20were%20on%20Friday%2C%20and%20that's%20positive%20for%20the%20markets%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-iran-strike-retaliation-stock-market-records-oil-jeremy-siegel-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1750686283000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a79944aab37011780b3672%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-iran-strike-retaliation-stock-market-records-oil-jeremy-siegel-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%2