ong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrep%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E10%20minutes%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECook%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E10%20minutes%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENutrition%20per%20portion%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFiber%3A%203.1%20grams%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EProtein%3A%2013%20grams%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIngredients%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E400%20grams%20(3%20cups%2F14%20ounces)%20white%20spelt%20or%20wholemeal%20flour%2C%20plus%20extra%20to%20dust%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E1%20tablespoon%20baking%20powder%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E1%20teaspoon%20sea%20salt%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E1%20teaspoon%20olive%20oil%2C%20plus%20extra%20for%20frying%20if%20needed%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E200%20grams%20(1%20cup%2F7%20ounces)%20skyr%2C%20Greek%20yogurt%2C%20or%20coconut%20yogurt%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOptional%20extras%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFreshly%20ground%20black%20pepper%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGrated%20garlic%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENigella%20seeds%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECumin%20seeds%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChopped%20coriander%20(cilantro)%20leaves%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESliced%20spring%20onion%20(scallion)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDesiccated%20(dried%2C%20shredded)%20coconut%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMethod%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E1.%20Combine%20the%20flour%2C%20baking%20powder%2C%20and%20salt%20in%20a%20bowl%2C%20then%20stir%20in%20the%20olive%20oil%20and%20yogurt%20(add%20any%20additional%20extras%20now%2C%20too).%20Mix%20with%20your%20hands%20until%20the%20dough%20comes%20together%2C%20then%20tip%20onto%20a%20flour-dusted%20surface%20and%20knead%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20minutes%20until%20you%20have%20a%20smooth%20dough.%20Divide%20the%20dough%20into%20six%20equal%20balls%2C%20cover%20with%20a%20clean%20tea%20(dish)%20towel%2C%20and%20allow%20to%20rest%20for%20at%20least%2010%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E2.%20Meanwhile%2C%20set%20a%20griddle%20pan%20or%20non-stick%20frying%20pan%20(skillet)%20over%20a%20high%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E3.%20Roll%20each%20dough%20ball%20into%20a%20flatbread%20shape%20about%2020%20centimeters%20(eight%20inches)%20long%20and%20two%20millimeters%20(1%E2%81%848%20inch)%20thick.%20If%20your%20pan%20isn't%20non-stick%20or%20you%20want%20a%20slightly%20crisp%20finish%20to%20your%20flatbreads%2C%20brush%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20flatbreads%20with%20a%20little%20olive%20oil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E4.%20When%20the%20pan%20is%20searingly%20hot%2C%20add%20a%20flatbread%20to%20the%20pan%20and%20cook%20for%2060%20to%2090%20seconds%20until%20char%20marks%20appear%2C%20then%20flip%20it%20over%20and%20cook%20the%20other%20side%20until%20nicely%20charred%20too.%20Wrap%20the%20flatbread%20in%20a%20tea%20(dish)%20towel%20while%20you%20cook%20the%20rest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225f2bc3e7-5399-4411-a1ee-7952a0fce3b5%5C%22%3ESeedy%20granola%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225334%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Seedy%20granola%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6842f36e9b2a601d01b27425%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%227997%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESeedy%20granola.%3Cp%3EClare%20Winfield%20%2FDorling%20Kindersley%3A%20Clare%20Winfield%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20such%20an%20adaptable%20recipe%20that%20you%20can%20make%20based%20on%20what%20you%20have%20in%20your%20store%20cupboard%20or%20your%20personal%20preferences%20for%20flavor%20and%20crunch.%20I%20love%20it%2C%20as%20it%20provides%20my%20family%20and%20me%20with%20lovely%20healthy%20fats%20and%20fibre%20for%20the%20day%20ahead.%20Serve%20as%20it%20is%20with%20your%20preferred%20milk%2C%20or%20top%20with%20fresh%20fruit%20and%20yogurt%2C%26quot%3B%20Lambert%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMakes%20about%20800%20grams%20(3.25%20pounds)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrep%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E25%20minutes%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECook%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E40%20minutes%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENutrition%20per%2040-gram%20portion%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFiber%3A%203.3%20grams%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EProtein%3A%205.3%20grams%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIngredients%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E175%20grams%20(6.5%20ounces)%20jumbo%20oats%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E175%20grams%20(6.5%20ounces)%20barley%2C%20spelt%2C%20or%20rye%20flakes%20(or%20simply%20use%20more%20jumbo%20oats)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E150%20grams%20(5.5%20ounces)%20nuts%2C%20roughly%20chopped%20(I%20use%20a%20mix%20of%20almonds%2C%20hazelnuts%2C%20pecans%2C%20and%20walnuts)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E150%20grams%20(5.5%20ounces)%20seeds%20(I%20use%20a%20mix%20of%20pumpkin%2C%20sunflower%2C%20sesame%2C%20and%20flaxseeds)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E1%20tablespoon%20ground%20cinnamon%2C%20nutmeg%2C%20ginger%2C%20or%20cardamom%20(or%20a%20mix)%20(optional)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E50%20grams%20(5%20tablespoons%2F1.75%20ounces)%20coconut%20oil%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E100%20grams%20(1%E2%81%843%20cup%2F3.5%20ounces)%20maple%20syrup%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E4%20tablespoons%20almond%20or%20peanut%20butter%20(optional)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E75%20grams%20(2.75%20ounces)%20organic*%20dried%20fruit%2C%20roughly%20chopped%20(I%20use%20a%20mix%20of%20dried%20apricots%2C%20figs%2C%20dates%2C%20cranberries%2C%20and%20sour%20cherries)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESea%20salt%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E*Select%20organic%20dried%20fruit%20to%20ensure%20it%20doesn't%20contain%20additives%20like%20sulphur%20dioxide%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMethod%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E1.%20Preheat%20the%20oven%20to%20160%C2%B0C%2F140%C2%B0C%20fan%2F325%C2%B0F%20and%20line%20your%20largest%20baking%20sheet%20with%20baking%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E2.%20Mix%20all%20the%20dry%20ingredients%20in%20a%20large%20bowl.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E3.%20Melt%20the%20coconut%20oil%20in%20a%20small%20saucepan%20over%20a%20low%20heat%20(or%20melt%20in%20the%20microwave%20for%2030%20seconds).%20Stir%20in%20the%20maple%20syrup%2C%20nut%20butter%20(if%20using)%2C%20and%20a%20pinch%20of%20salt%2C%20then%20mix%20until%20fully%20combined.%20Pour%20over%20the%20dry%20ingredients%20and%20stir%20until%20everything%20is%20nicely%20coated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E4.%20Spread%20out%20in%20an%20even%20layer%20on%20the%20baking%20sheet%20and%20bake%20for%2030%20to%2035%20minutes%20until%20golden%2C%20stirring%20and%20tossing%20occasionally%20so%20that%20it%20cooks%20evenly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E5.%20Leave%20to%20cool%20on%20the%20tray%2C%20then%20stir%20in%20the%20dried%20fruit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E6.%20Store%20in%20an%20airtight%20container%20at%20room%20temperature%20for%20up%20to%20one%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENote%3A%20You%20can%20cook%20this%20using%20your%20air%20fryer%20too.%20Heat%20the%20air%20fryer%20to%20160%C2%B0C%2F325%C2%B0F%20and%20air%20fry%20for%2010%20to%2012%20minutes%2C%20tossing%20occasionally.%20You%20may%20need%20to%20air%20fry%20the%20granola%20in%20two%20batches%20depending%20on%20the%20size%20of%20your%20air%20fryer%2C%20for%20ultimate%20crispness.%20It%20will%20crisp%20up%20further%20as%20it%20cools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a6c5e0e2-7e0e-414c-9cd1-93705db9751b%5C%22%3EChocolate%2C%20peanut%2C%20and%20date%20bars%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225334%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chocolate%2C%20peanut%2C%20and%20date%20bars%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6842f4149b2a601d01b2743b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%227997%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChocolate%2C%20peanut%2C%20and%20date%20bars.%3Cp%3EClare%20Winfield%20%2FDorling%20Kindersley%3A%20Clare%20Winfield%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSticky%2C%20nutty%2C%20and%20chocolatey%2C%20these%20are%20the%20ultimate%20pick-me-up.%20You%20can%20slice%20these%20into%20smaller%20bars%20if%20you%20like%2C%20but%20be%20aware%20that%20you%20may%20need%20a%20little%20more%20chocolate%20to%20coat%20all%20of%20them.%20In%20the%20summer%2C%20I%20love%20to%20eat%20these%20straight%20out%20of%20the%20freezer%20sprinkled%20with%20a%20tiny%20pinch%20of%20flaky%20salt%2C%26quot%3B%20Lambert%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMakes%20about%2015%20bars%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrep%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E20%20minutes%20(plus%20freezing)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECook%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efive%20minutes%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENutrition%20per%20bar%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFibre%3A%203.3%20grams%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EProtein%3A%205%20grams%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIngredients%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E75%20grams%20(3%E2%81%844%20cup%2F2.75%20ounces)%20jumbo%20or%20rolled%20oats%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E300%20grams%20(10.5%20ounces)%20pitted%20Medjool%20dates%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E4%20tablespoons%20smooth%20peanut%20butter%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E1.5%20teaspoons%20vanilla%20extract%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E0.25%20teaspoon%20sea%20salt%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E80%20grams%20(2.75%20ounces)%20unsalted%20roasted%20peanuts%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E175%20grams%20(6.25%20ounces)%20dark%20(bittersweet)%20chocolate%20(at%20least%2075%25%20cocoa%20solids)%2C%20broken%20into%20small%20pieces%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E2%20teaspoons%20coconut%20oil%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMethod%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E1.%20Line%20a%2020-centimeter%20(8-inch)%20square%20cake%20pan%20with%20baking%20paper%2C%20with%20plenty%20of%20overhang.%20Place%20the%20oats%20in%20a%20blender%20or%20food%20processor%20and%20blitz%20to%20a%20fine%20flour%2C%20then%20tip%20into%20a%20bowl%20and%20set%20aside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E2.%20Place%20the%20dates%20in%20the%20blender%20or%20food%20processor%20(no%20need%20to%20clean%20it)%20with%20the%20peanut%20butter%2C%20vanilla%2C%20and%20salt.%20Roughly%20blitz%2C%20then%20slowly%20add%2075%20milliliters%20(five%20tablespoons%2F2.5%20fluid%20ounces)%20of%20water%20until%20you%20have%20a%20smooth%2C%20thick%20paste.%20Be%20sure%20to%20scrape%20down%20the%20sides%20occasionally.%20Remove%20300%20grams%20(10.5%20ounces)%20of%20the%20date%20mix%20to%20a%20bowl%20and%20set%20aside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E3.%20Add%20the%20oat%20flour%20back%20to%20the%20blender%20or%20food%20processor%20with%20the%20remaining%20date%20mix%20and%20pulse%20a%20few%20times%20until%20it's%20nicely%20combined.%20Tip%20the%20mixture%20into%20the%20base%20of%20the%20lined%20pan%20and%20use%20wet%20fingertips%20to%20spread%20it%20into%20a%20smooth%20layer%20that%20fills%20the%20tin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E4.%20Spread%20the%20remaining%20date%20mixture%20on%20top%2C%20smoothing%20it%20with%20a%20spatula.%20Evenly%20sprinkle%20over%20the%20nuts%2C%20pushing%20them%20in%20a%20little.%20Place%20in%20the%20freezer%20for%20at%20least%20six%20hours%20or%20ideally%20overnight%20until%20frozen%20and%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E5.%20Lift%20the%20frozen%20slab%20out%20of%20the%20pan%20and%20slice%20into%2015%20bars.%20Line%20a%20baking%20sheet%20with%20baking%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E6.%20Add%20the%20chocolate%20and%20coconut%20oil%20to%20a%20heatproof%20bowl%20set%20over%20a%20pan%20of%20barely%20simmering%20water%20and%20heat%20until%20just%20melted%2C%20stirring%20to%20combine.%20Alternatively%2C%20heat%20in%20a%20microwave%20on%20the%20lowest%20setting%20in%2030-second%20blasts%2C%20stirring%20between%20each%2C%20until%20just%20melted.%20If%20you%20have%20a%20cooking%20thermometer%2C%20the%20chocolate%20is%20ready%20when%20it%20reads%2045%20to%2050%C2%B0C%20(113%20to%20122%C2%B0F).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E7.%20Working%20one%20at%20a%20time%2C%20submerge%20the%20bars%20in%20the%20melted%20chocolate%2C%20using%20two%20forks%20to%20turn%20them.%20Lift%20out%20of%20the%20bowl%20using%20the%20forks%2C%20allowing%20the%20excess%20chocolate%20to%20drip%20back%20into%20the%20bowl%2C%20then%20transfer%20them%20to%20the%20lined%20sheet.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20all%20the%20bars%20are%20coated%20in%20chocolate%2C%20return%20the%20sheet%20to%20the%20freezer%20or%20fridge%20for%20at%20least%2015%20minutes%20until%20the%20chocolate%20is%20set.%20Store%20in%20an%20airtight%20container%20in%20the%20fridge%20for%20up%20to%20two%20weeks%20or%20freezer%20for%20up%20to%20four%20weeks%2C%20but%20I%20assure%20you%20they%20won't%20last%20long!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENote%3A%20If%20you%20can't%20find%20roasted%20peanuts%2C%20simply%20use%20unroasted%20peanuts%20and%20roast%20them%20in%20the%20oven%20at%20180%C2%B0%2F160%C2%B0fan%2F350%C2%B0F%20for%20eight%20to%2012%20minutes%20until%20golden.%20Then%20use%20in%20the%20recipe%20as%20specified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsimple-recipes-eating-fewer-ultra-processed-foods-easy-nutritionist-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1750671821000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6842f4fd9b2a601d01b27462%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsimple-recipes-eating-fewer-ultra-processed-foods-easy-nutritionist-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ultra-processed%20foods%20are%20convenient%20but%20we%20should%20eat%20them%20in%20moderation%2C%20the%20nutritionist%20Rhiannon%20Lambert%20said.%20She%20shared%20her%20recipes%20for%20flatbreads%2C%20granola%2C%20and%20chocolate%20bars.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22rhosie%40businessinsider.com%20(Rachel%20Hosie)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsimple-recipes-eating-fewer-ultra-processed-foods-easy-nutritionist-2025-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Sitaare%20Zameen%20Par'%20box%20office%20collection%20day%204%20(LIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1750671050000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-122022063%2Cimgsize-44970.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fbox-office%2Fsitaare-zameen-par-box-office-collection-day-4-live-the-aamir-khan-starrer-begins-monday-on-a-decent-note-after-a-huge-gro