0Tehran's%20retaliation%20and%20oil%20disruption.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFor%20years%2C%20Tehran%20has%20threatened%20to%20close%20the%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz%2C%20a%20key%20energy%20shipping%20route%20to%20its%20south.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20blockade%20would%20hit%20Asian%20markets%20hardest%2C%20with%20global%20high%20prices%20also%20affecting%20the%20US.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGlobal%20investors%20are%20on%20alert%20about%20a%2090-mile%20sea%20passage%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20fearing%20that%20any%20block%20of%20the%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz%20could%20derail%20global%20shipping%20and%20oil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETensions%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20escalated%20sharply%20after%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-struck-iran-with-most-elusive-weapons-stealth-bombers-submarine-2025-6%3Futm_medium%3Dingest%26utm_source%3Dmarkets%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EUS%20struck%20Iran's%20nuclear%20facilities%20%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3Eon%20Sunday%2C%20prompting%20fears%20of%20retaliation%20from%20Tehran.%20Beyond%20concerns%20about%20defense%20and%20security%2C%20markets%20are%20concerned%20about%20the%20fallout%20for%20oil%20prices%20and%20the%20global%20economy%20should%20Iran%20block%20shipping%20in%20the%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz%20%E2%80%94%20a%20threat%20Tehran%20has%20repeated%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Iran%20chooses%20to%20blockade%20the%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz%2C%20it'd%20be%20categorically%20negative%2C%26quot%3B%20Kyle%20Rodda%2C%20a%20senior%20financial%20markets%20analyst%20at%20Capital.com%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20worst-case%20scenario%2C%20it%20would%20be%20incredibly%20impactful%3A%20higher%20fuel%20prices%2C%20higher%20inflation%2C%20slower%20growth%2C%20and%20interest%20rates%20higher%20than%20where%20they'd%20otherwise%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20Rodda%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2263a6a888-6304-4ede-9afe-1dae855eeb3f%5C%22%3EWhat%20is%20the%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FUAKuW%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20map%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20showing%20the%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz%20in%20the%20Persian%20Gulf%2C%20with%20Iran%20highlighted%20and%20markers%20on%20Dubai%20and%20Tehran.%20%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FUAKuW%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20geopolitically%20sensitive%20maritime%20routes%2C%20the%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz%20is%20just%2021%20miles%20across%20at%20its%20narrowest%20point.%20It%20connects%20the%20Persian%20Gulf%20to%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%2C%20with%20Iran%20to%20its%20north%20and%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20and%20Oman%20to%20its%20south.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20US's%20Energy%20Information%20Administration%2C%20the%20Hormuz%20is%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20busiest%20shipping%20lanes%2C%20carrying%20about%2020%20million%20barrels%20of%20oil%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20energy%20shipments%20through%20the%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz%20have%20no%20other%20means%20of%20exiting%20the%20Persian%20Gulf%2C%20the%20starting%20sea%20point%20for%20major%20oil%20producers%20like%20Saudi%20Arabia%20to%20export%20their%20energy%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223e1f22a5-d9b5-489a-b1c4-509637f48445%5C%22%3EHow%20much%20shipping%20goes%20through%20the%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20a%20quarter%20of%20seaborne%20oil%20and%20a%20fifth%20of%20global%20liquified%20natural%20gas%20trade%20moves%20through%20the%20Hormuz%2C%20so%20any%20disruption%20to%20shipping%20would%20hit%20the%20energy%20markets%20hard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20bombing%20of%20Iranian%20nuclear%20facilities%20by%20the%20US%20over%20the%20weekend%20increased%20supply%20risks%20significantly%20for%20the%20oil%20and%20LNG%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Warren%20Patterson%2C%20the%20head%20of%20commodities%20strategy%20at%20ING%2C%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222b3535f2-19e2-4065-a757-7278313ab255%5C%22%3ECan%20Iran%20really%20close%20the%20Strait%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIran%20doesn't%20have%20the%20legal%20authority%20to%20shut%20down%20marine%20traffic%20in%20the%20Hormuz.%20But%20it%20could%20disrupt%20the%20movement%20of%20vessels%20by%20other%20means%2C%20for%20example%20by%20damaging%20oil%20and%20shipping%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Sunday%2C%20the%20Iranian%20parliament%20voted%20to%20close%20the%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz%20in%20retaliation%20against%20the%20US's%20action.%20The%20final%20decision%20still%20lies%20with%20the%20country's%20top%20security%20officials%2C%20according%20to%20Iran's%20state-owned%20Press%20TV.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20said%20they%20think%20an%20Iranian%20blockade%20is%20probably%20more%20about%20political%20posturing%20than%20real%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20the%20headlines%20sound%20dramatic%2C%20the%20reality%20is%20that%20Iran's%20parliament%20holds%20no%20executive%20power%20over%20military%20or%20strategic%20decisions%2C%20particularly%20not%20ones%20with%20such%20far-reaching%20geopolitical%20and%20economic%20consequences%2C%26quot%3B%20Dilin%20Wu%2C%20a%20research%20strategist%20at%20Pepperstone%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIran%20is%20well%20aware%20that%20any%20direct%20disruption%20to%20global%20oil%20flows%20through%20the%20Strait%20would%20likely%20trigger%20a%20significant%20military%20and%20economic%20response%2C%20possibly%20escalating%20the%20conflict%20beyond%20its%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227604f418-9ea0-4ac0-aa03-daddde36a7b3%5C%22%3EWould%20the%20US%20be%20affected%20by%20a%20blockade%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20is%20an%20energy%20giant%20and%20has%20become%20a%20net%20energy%20exporter%20since%202019%2C%20so%20it's%20less%20prone%20to%20physical%20supply%20shock%20from%20a%20blockade%20of%20the%20Hormuz.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20US%20could%20still%20be%20hit%20by%20the%20fallout%20from%20worsening%20global%20economic%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20negative%20impact%20would%20be%20through%20deteriorating%20financial%20conditions%C2%A0or%20through%20higher%20for%20longer%20rates%20as%20the%20Fed%20has%20another%20reason%20to%20delay%20cuts%2C%26quot%3B%20Deutsche%20Bank%20analysts%20said%20in%20a%20Monday%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2274235857-c59a-459b-bf5f-ac5bf5834e39%5C%22%3EWhat%20about%20other%20countries%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAsian%20countries%20would%20be%20the%20most%20affected%20by%20a%20blockade%20of%20the%20Hormuz%2C%20said%20Priyanka%20Sachdeva%2C%20a%20senior%20analyst%20at%20brokerage%20Phillip%20Nova.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20over%2080%25%20of%20crude%20oil%2C%20condensates%2C%20and%20LNG%20that%20moved%20through%20the%20Hormuz%20headed%20to%20Asia%2C%20according%20to%20the%20EIA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAsia%2C%20which%20consumes%20the%20lion's%20share%20of%20Middle%20Eastern%20oil%2C%20would%20be%20most%20vulnerable%2C%20with%20India%2C%20Japan%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20and%20China%20facing%20logistical%20uncertainties%20and%20costlier%20re-routing%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sachdeva.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20a%20third%20of%20the%20oil%20that%20passed%20through%20the%20Hormuz%20headed%20to%20China%2C%20Bloomberg%20calculated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESouth%20European%20countries%20dependent%20on%20Gulf%20oil%20could%20also%20face%20higher%20import%20costs%2C%20although%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20the%20UAE%20can%20reroute%20significant%20volumes%20of%20such%20exports%20via%20pipelines%20and%20via%20a%20pipeline%20and%20the%20UAE%20port%20of%20Fujairah.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e1d90324-e234-4b91-884f-2588a7f0fd6e%5C%22%3EWhat%20would%20a%20closure%20mean%20for%20gas%20prices%20and%20inflation%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEnergy%20is%20a%20key%20input%20cost%2C%20so%20any%20gains%20in%20oil%20prices%20are%20likely%20to%20drive%20up%20inflation%20broadly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US's%20strike%20on%20Iran%20sent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fcommodities%2Foil-price%3Ftype%3Dwti%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eoil%20futures%3C%2Fa%3E%20up%20to%20a%20five-month%20high%20late%20on%20Sunday.%20Oil%20prices%20are%20now%20up%20about%2010%25%20since%20Israel's%20strikes%20on%20Iran%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20developments%20are%20taking%20place%20amid%20the%20summer%20driving%20season%2C%20when%20US%20gas%20demand%20peaks.%20Should%20the%20gains%20in%20oil%20prices%20be%20sustained%2C%20pump%20prices%20are%20likely%20to%20rise%20in%20the%20weeks%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20EIA%2C%20the%20price%20of%20gas%20typically%20rises%20by%202.4%20cents%20per%20gallon%20when%20crude%20oil%20prices%20rise%20by%20%241.%20This%20translates%20into%20a%20gain%20of%20about%2020%20cents%20per%20gallon%20at%20current%20levels%20for%20oil%20futures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Firan-strait-of-hormuz-important-for-global-oil-prices-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1750671013000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6858f46d3d5881a51c1bda37%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Firan-strait-of-hormuz-important-for-global-oil-prices-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz%20is%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20busiest%20shipping%20lanes%2C%20so%20any%20disruption%20would%20hit%20the%20energy%20markets%20hard.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22htan%40insider.com%20(Huileng%20Tan%2CPete%20Syme)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A120%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fww